        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         Well, the new people at Verant have stated that they are trying to remove many of the old philosophies of the previous developers. On comment was that they prefer to "under-promise, and over-deliver". Frankly I appreciate that and respect it. They were pretty tight lipped about the bazaar and the new UI. They didn't make a lot of promises about them, and didn't even go into detail of what would be offered. They produced well more than I could have hoped for in both. It allowed me to put a small amount of faith back into the dev team. </P><P>I'd prefer to hear nothing and be pleasently suprised, than not get things that they said they <i>might</i> be able to get in.</P><P>For the spells that we've seen:<BR>The dots do look like crap. There doesn't seem to be a progression at all, just a variety. I don't find variety to be an appropriate reward for effort. </P><P>The pets, however, I have hope for. Where 1 or 2 of these pets may be situational, I can see the SK pet being fantastic. Should have reasonable ac/hp, and a harmtouch every so often would be fantastic. If the HT is on a mob timer reset, it's available every 12-15 minutes isn't it? And if they make our pets more powerful, you can bet that they'll make the mage pets more so. </P><P>Getting the spells has me worried. I don't want to find that they're all drops from the gods. There should be reasonable ability for somewhat casual players to get them without forking out 100kpp.</P><P> <a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
