         The only reason to even get a Necro epic is for the DOT/Snare effect (which is very nice).  Staff of the Silent Star is a clear upgrade, and it drops off a gimpy NToV mob.  When I got mine, 2 dropped, and the second rotted because nobody wanted to spend points on it (read - it wasn't really an upgrade for anyone else).</P><P>The sad irony with player epics is that by the time you are powerful enough to get one, you likely already have access to better items.</P><P>I know this isn't an epic specific thread, but the two issues are related.  Mudflation has really taken a toll on EQ this past year, and yet again it would appear to me that casters got the shit end of the stick having to upgrade both items and spells to be effective in Luclin encounters.  And it seems it may get much worse in PoP.</P><P></P><P>Xuraz Xorthexia - <BR>Warlock<BR>Xegony Server<BR>Profile - <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=72377" target="_blank">http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=72377</a></P><P>"They call us walking corpses, unholy living dead.<BR>They had to lock us up, put us in their pretty jails." - The Misfits</P><P>Edited by - Xuraz on 09/16/2002  14:20:02<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
