        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         Warblek - Yeah, going from 44 to 49 was definitely cool. But sub-50 levels can be done several times over in a day, and you get a LOT of spells. Now we're looking at 5 uber hell levels for a small handful of spells, which are all upgrades of our existing spells? Ugh. Haven't we done enough leveling and gotten the same spells with more mana cost and damage enough? I'd like something new, or insanely superior to what we have now. Like a 5k dot for 500 mana. Crazy you say? Not at all. It'd put spells in line with weapons as far as mudflation. Melee weapons have more than doubled in efficiency since the beginning of EQ, why haven't spells done the same?<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
